<title></title>
README

<p>
RealTimeBattle is a programming game for Unix, in which robots
controlled by programs are fighting each other. The goal is to destroy
the enemies, using the radar to examine the environment and the cannon
to shoot.

RealTimeBattle is open source software, distributed under the General
Public License (GPL). Read more about this license in the file <tt>COPYING</tt>.

For info on installation, read the file <tt>INSTALL</tt>.

More information on usage, construction of robots and more can be
found in the user manual in the subdirectory <tt>Documentation</tt>.



There are two mailing-lists for RealTimeBattle. One for announcements and
the other for discussions.

The announcement-list is called <newline>
<url name="realtimebattle-announce"
url="mailto:realtimebattle-announce@lists.sourceforge.net">.
It is a moderated low traffic list where only posts of general interest to
RealTimeBattle users get through. Here will, for example, new releases and
competitions be announced.

To subscribe, unsubscribe or set your preferences, go to <newline>
<url name="the web interface"
url="http://lists.sourceforge.net/mailman/listinfo/realtimebattle-announce">.
There is also an email-based interface, for help send an email to <newline>
<url name="realtimebattle-announce-request@lists.sourceforge.net"
url="mailto:realtimebattle-announce-request@lists.sourceforge.net">
with just the word 'help' in the subject or body.

The discussion-list is called <newline>
<url name="realtimebattle-discussion"
url="mailto:realtimebattle-discussion@lists.sourceforge.net">.

Here can anything related to RealTimeBattle be discussed. It is not moderated.

To subscribe, unsubscribe or set your preferences, go to <newline>
<url name="the web interface"
url="http://lists.sourceforge.net/mailman/listinfo/realtimebattle-discussion">.
There is also an email-based interface, for help send an email to <newline>
<url name="realtimebattle-discussion-request@lists.sourceforge.net"
url="mailto:realtimebattle-discussion-request@lists.sourceforge.net">
with just the word 'help' in the subject or body.

If you encounter a bug or some problem of any sort, please look in the
files <tt>BUGS</tt>, <tt>TODO</tt> and <tt>FAQ</tt> in this directory,
as well as the corresponding pages at the 
<url name="RealTimeBattle homepage" url="http://www.lysator.liu.se/realtimebattle">.

Comments, bug reports and/or patches can be sent to the email address
<htmlurl name="rtb@users.sourceforge.net" url="mailto:rtb@users.sourceforge.net">

Hope you will enjoy your time using the program!

</notes>



